reviewText: This was a very good movie. I really liked the acting and the black and white. One of my favorites.

LIZ SCOTT AND PAUL HEINREID USUALLY DO WELL IN THEIR ACTING, BUT THIS FILM IS A LET DOWN AND SEEMS A FEMALE VERSION OF PAUL FILM "THE SCAR".  ITS TOO BAD BECAUSE I WAS REALLY LOOKING FORWARD TO A ENJOYABLE AFTERNOON WITH THIS FILM, BUT FOUND MYSELF LOOKING IN THE LIBRARY FOR ANOTHER FILM.
